pter is preceded by a short introduction that lays out the context in which the piece was written. Drawing on his own memories as a former athlete, informal observations of his children's sports activities, and more formal research such as life-history interviews with athletes and content analyses of sports media, Michael A. Messner presents a multifaceted picture of gender constructed through an array of personalities, institutions, cultural symbols, and everyday interactions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAthletes in mass media. 0aMasculinity in sports. 0aSex discrimination in sports. 0aSex role. 0aSportsxSocial aspects. 0aTelevision and sports. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aConnell, Raewyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunbar, Michele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuncan, Margaret Carlisle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Darnell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomon, William S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWillms, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade Oca, Jeffrey Montez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147978040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791479780423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791479780/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles